at the dawn of videogaming, when we were all kids just typing in our
games, one line of BASIC at a time. And he finds the present lacking:
'The dreamers became assets instead of leaders, and the rockstar
designers became, well, Rockstar ... or Blizzard, or Valve. Publishers
with cash-rich money to spend bought the creative process, and the minds
of marketing professionals replaced four guys hopped up on sugar
spiehnuts and generic cola. So, how dare I be surprised that the price of
today's gaming blitz is a little piece of last generation's soul?' Do you
agree? Was simple gaming better, or are you a story in games fan?"

