[0]andrew cooke writes "[1]Java 6 was recently released, but many
programmers are still exploring the features introduced in Java 5 —
probably the most significant changes in the language's twelve year
history. Amongst those changes (enumerations, auto-boxing, foreach,
varargs) generics was the most far-reaching, introducing generic
programming in a simpler, safer way than C++ templates and, unlike
generics in C#, maintaining backwards (and forwards) compatibility with
existing Java code." Read on for the rest of Andrew's review.

