| Brain Tumor Vaccine Shows Promising Results                        |
|   from the getting-a-head-of-cancer dept.                          |
|   posted by ScuttleMonkey on Monday April 16, @14:53 (Science)     |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/16/170257       |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

ScienceDaily is reporting that a new vaccine used in the treatment of a
cancer found primarliy in the brain is [0]showing promising results after
an initial trial at the University of California. "Of the 12 patients
being treated, eight can currently be evaluated for overall survival,
while four are still receiving treatment. Seven out of the eight patients
have exceeded the historical median benchmark of 6.5 months survival from
time of recurrence. The investigators will continue to follow the
patients for overall survival. Based on these results, a larger,
multi-center phase 2 study is planned for late 2007."

