+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Firefox Usage Near 25% In Europe                                   |
|   from the edge-of-the-wedge dept.                                 |
|   posted by kdawson on Monday April 16, @19:28 (Mozilla)           |
|   http://it.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/16/2151218           |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]PARENA writes "French researcher Xiti claims that Mozilla [1]Firefox
keeps winning terrain in Europe. 24.1% of Internet users in Europe use
Firefox. Slovenia (44.5%), Finland (41.3%), Croatia (36.5%), and Germany
(36.2%) lead the way, followed by a group of mostly Eastern European
countries. Remarkably, The Netherlands is only at 13.3%, right before
Andorra. Oceania maintains a slight lead over Europe, at 24.8%; the rest
of the world trails at 11.9% to 15.1%."

